      <body>
         <div>
         <head>Request to <choice><orig>Cupide</orig><reg>Cupid</reg></choice> for <choice><orig>reuenge</orig><reg>revenge</reg></choice> of his <choice><orig>vnkinde</orig><reg>unkind</reg></choice> <choice><orig>loue</orig><reg>love</reg></choice>.</head>
         <lg type="sonnet">
            <l n="1">Behold, <choice><orig>Loue</orig><reg>Love</reg></choice>, thy power how she despiseth: </l>
            <l n="2">My <choice><orig>greuous</orig><reg>grevious</reg></choice> <choice><orig>payn</orig><reg>pain</reg></choice> how litle she regardeth,</l>
            <l n="3">The <choice><orig>solemne</orig><reg>solemn</reg></choice> <choice><orig>othe</orig><reg>oath</reg></choice>, <choice><orig>wherof</orig><reg>whereof</reg></choice> she takes no cure, </l>
            <l n="4">Broken she hath: and yet, she <choice><orig>bydeth</orig><reg>bideth</reg></choice> sure,</l>
            <l n="5">Right at her ease, and <choice><orig>litle</orig><reg>little</reg></choice> thee she <choice><orig>dredeth</orig><reg>dreadeth</reg></choice>.</l>
            <l n="6">Weaponed thou art, and she <choice><orig>vnarmed</orig><reg>unarmed</reg></choice> sitteth:</l>
            <l n="7">To the disdainful, all her life she leadeth:</l>
            <l n="8">To me spiteful, without <choice><orig>iust</orig><reg>just</reg></choice> cause, or measure.</l>
            <l n="9">Behold <choice><orig>Loue</orig><reg>Love</reg></choice>, how proudly she triumpheth,</l>
            <l n="10">I am in hold, but if thee pitie <choice><orig>meueth</orig><reg>moveth</reg></choice>:</l>
            <l n="11">Go, bend thy bow, that stony <choice><orig>hartes</orig><reg>hearts</reg></choice> breaketh:</l>
            <l n="12">And with some stroke <choice><orig>reuenge</orig><reg>revenge</reg></choice> the great displeasure</l>
            <l n="13">Of thee, and him that <choice><orig>sorow</orig><reg>sorrow</reg></choice> doth endure,</l>
            <l n="14">And as his Lord thee lowly here entreateth.</l>
         </lg>
         <note type="translation" resp="#jawalsh">Translation of <title rendition="#i">Rvf</title> 121  by Thomas Wyatt (1521?-1554), from <title rendition="#i">Tottel’s Miscellany</title> (1557).</note>
         </div>
